{
  "message": "test(ansi): add insta snapshot fixtures for ANSI sequence tests\n\nThis commit adds insta snapshot files that verify ANSI escape sequence\noutput for color modes, cursor control, hyperlinks, and text attributes.\n\nsrc/ansi/snapshots/ - Test Snapshots:\nColor Mode Snapshots:\n- snapshot_fg_colors_truecolor.snap: 24-bit RGB foreground sequences\n- snapshot_fg_colors_256.snap: 256-color palette foreground\n- snapshot_fg_colors_16.snap: Basic 16-color foreground\n- snapshot_fg_colors_nocolor.snap: No-color fallback mode\n- snapshot_bg_colors_truecolor.snap: 24-bit RGB background sequences\n- snapshot_bg_colors_256.snap: 256-color palette background\n- snapshot_bg_colors_16.snap: Basic 16-color background\n\nCursor Control Snapshots:\n- snapshot_cursor_position.snap: Absolute cursor positioning\n- snapshot_cursor_move.snap: Relative cursor movement sequences\n\nFeature Snapshots:\n- snapshot_hyperlinks.snap: OSC 8 hyperlink sequences\n- snapshot_text_attributes.snap: Bold, italic, underline, etc.\n\nPurpose:\n- Regression testing for ANSI output\n- Ensures sequences match terminal specifications\n- Human-readable expected output format\n- Updates via: cargo insta review\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
